messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
My neighbor's house is burning down at 312 Washington Avenue.
Is anybody inside?
I don't know. I'm finding out right now.
Okay, we are on our way. Keep everyone away from the house.
They said stay away from the house. Is everybody out?
They're getting somebody out right now. They're looking for the little boy, Avon.
How old is he?
There's an 18-month-old baby in there.
18-month-old?
Yes.
We need help immediately.
We've already dispatched help, okay? Let me know when they get him out, or if they have gotten him out.
They're going in for the baby.
Okay, I don't want anybody getting hurt.
Well, they're going in anyway for the baby. The mom just passed out.
Is she outside?
Yes, but she's tough.
No, she's up. The baby's inside the house.
He's only 18 months old and the whole house is going up.
Do we know where he's at in the house?
They don't know where he is. They're trying to get him.
Okay, let me know what happens.
They haven't got him yet. They can't get the door open. Okay, bam. They got the door open.
We already have help on the way. Let me know what's going on.
The whole house is burning down. We're trying to put it out with our hose, but if you don't hurry, we're going to lose our house.
We can't come any faster than with lights and sirens. We're coming as fast as we can.
I know. Oh my God. There's black smoke everywhere.
I'm so sorry. We are on our way. Just take a deep breath for me.
Oh my God. They've got about 15 people going in to get the baby.
They don't need all those people going in there. It's dangerous.
Well, they're going in. They're looking in every room. Oh my God, he's only 18 months.
They can't get in there. They can't get in to where the baby is.
We've already sent help. Can you stay outside?
I can't find my way. Nobody can get in. Oh my God.
Help is on the way. Keep everyone away from the house.
We're trying. They aren't listening. My house might burn down too. Bye.
Stay safe. Help is on the way.
